<TITLE> Court turns down appeals for Tarique bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 14 (bdnews24.com) -A Dhaka court Thursday turned down bail appeals of Tarique Rahman in four extortion cases. The Dhaka Metropolitan Sessions Judge`s Court heard appeals in the cases filed with Gulshan and Dhanmondi police stations against the elder son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia. Businessmen Harun Ferdousi, Aftab Uddin and Syed Abu Shahed Sohel filed three cases with Gulshan Police Station while contractor Mir Zahir Hossain filed the fourth with Dhanmondi Police Station. Judge Md Azizul Haque turned down the petitions. Meanwhile, the First Additional Judge's Court, Dhaka Thursday recorded testimonies of four witnesses in the arms case against Tarique's business partner Giasuddin Al Mamun. bdnews24
